<br>
It is not intentional for pet classes, but we suffer the side effect.  To make fights more interesting and areas dangerous, NPCs have to follow strange paths to agro a few more so it's not a simple pull and kill contest.  So when you see an NPC run away and return with a few more, I think it's by design.  The pet tends to follow the paths of NPC, so it will follow the strange agro route and collect things.  It is unfortunate but nothing we can do about it.  By fixing the pathing, they will lower the difficulty of a dungeon.<br>
